  <front>
    <title>Route Distinguisher Zero Value Usage</title>
    <seriesInfo name="Internet-Draft" value="draft-martini-l3vpn-rd-zero-00"/>
    <author initials="L." surname="Martini" fullname="Luca Martini">
      <organization>Cisco Systems Inc.</organization>
    </author>
    <author initials="K." surname="Patel" fullname="Keyur Patel">
      <organization>Cisco Systems Inc.</organization>
    </author>
    <date day="10" month="October" year="2006"/>
    <abstract>
      <t>   The behaviour that must be followed when an route distinguisher (RD)
   of value zero is received is not clearly defined in rfc4364. This
   document clarifies the use of an RD with a value of zero in the
   context defined in rfc 4364.

	 </t>
    </abstract>
